                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 818.00/123</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-02T16:00:00-05:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 2, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Election held yesterday without disorder or opposition. Government claims fifty
                    thousand plurality total electorate of seventy thousand. Voluntary vote small.
                    Reports of flagrant ballot box stuffing. No enthusiasm and strong reactionary
                    feeling apparent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hale</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
